The best hyper-parameter values are determined through grid search,
maximizing the recall metric in Stage 1 and the R@P50 metric in Stage 2 (or alternatively AUC).
This is done for two modes: a single {\em global} value for a hyper-parameter, or {\em per-predicate} values, specific for each P.